Project Overview

The objective of this project was to design an interactive healthcare analytics dashboard that explores patient admissions, demographics, medical conditions, and billing patterns.

The project emphasizes end-to-end analytical thinking, from data preparation and modeling to insight-driven visualization design. Although the final dashboard was built in Power BI, this document outlines the analytical workflow, business reasoning, and technical decisions involved.

Tools Used - Power BI - DAX - Power Query - R Markdown (documentation)

Dataset Description

The dataset consists of 10,000 synthetic patient records, structured to resemble real-world hospital data.

Key attributes include: - Patient demographics (age, gender, blood type) - Medical conditions and test results - Admission and discharge dates - Insurance providers - Billing amounts - Admission types (e.g., emergency, elective)

Data Preparation & Modeling

Data Cleaning (Power Query)

  • Corrected data types for dates, numeric values, and currency fields
  • Created a Length of Stay variable using admission and discharge dates
  • Validated values to ensure realistic hospital stay durations

Date Table Creation

A dedicated Date Table was created to enable proper time-based analysis.

DateTable <- seq(
  from = as.Date("min(Date of Admission)"),
  to   = as.Date("max(Date of Admission)"),
  by   = "day"
)

Measures & Calculations

Total Admissions = COUNTROWS(healthcare_dataset)
Avg Length of Stay = AVERAGE(healthcare_dataset[Length of Stay])
Total Billing Amount = SUM(healthcare_dataset[Billing Amount])
Avg Billing per Admission = DIVIDE([Total Billing Amount], [Total Admissions])

Visual Analysis & Insights

Admissions Over Time

A line chart was used to analyze trends in hospital admissions by MonthYear.

Top Medical Conditions

A ranked bar chart highlighted conditions driving the highest admission volume.

Admissions by Age Group & Gender

A stacked column chart revealed demographic patterns.

Billing Distribution by Insurance Provider

A treemap displayed proportional contribution to total billing.
